<body>
    <h1>DevOps on Linux Project - Weather VM Project</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-Overview">Overview<=
/h2>
<p>This project automates a VM to fetch and display current weather informa=
tion for a chosen city on startup and at login.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-=F0=9F=8E=AFProjectGoal">=
=F0=9F=8E=AF Project Goal</h2>
<p>Automate your VM so that it fetches the current weather for a chosen cit=
y on startup and shows it at login.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-=E2=9C=85Requirements">=E2=
=9C=85 Requirements</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-EnvironmentConfiguration">E=
nvironment Configuration</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Store the city name in <code>/etc/default/weather</code> using a variabl=
e:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: jscript; gutter: false; theme: Django" data-theme=3D"Django">CITY=3DTimis=
oara
</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
<li>
<p>Script must read the <code>CITY</code> environment variable and default =
to "Timisoara" if not set</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-WeatherScript">Weather Scri=
pt</h3>
<p><strong>Location:</strong> <code>/usr/local/sbin/weather.sh</code></p>
<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Install required packages (<code>curl</code>, <code>jq</code>) if missin=
g</p></li>
<li>
<p>Fetch weather from <code>wttr.in/$CITY</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Generate a clean <code>/etc/motd</code> with:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Project header ("Welcome to your Dev VM")</p></li>
<li>
<p>City name</p></li>
<li>
<p>Weather info</p></li>
<li>
<p>Hostname + current time</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Script must be idempotent (overwrite MOTD, no duplication)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-systemdService">systemd Ser=
vice</h3>
<p><strong>Location:</strong> <code>/etc/systemd/system/weather.service</co=
de></p>
<p><strong>Configuration:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Runs <code>weather.sh</code> at boot</p></li>
<li>
<p>Loads environment variables from <code>/etc/default/weather</code></p></=
li>
<li>
<p>Type: <code>oneshot</code>, <code>RemainAfterExit=3Dyes</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-=F0=9F=94=8DVerification">=
=F0=9F=94=8D Verification</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-ExpectedOutput">Expected Ou=
tput</h3>
<p>On login or with <code>cat /etc/motd</code>, students should see:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: jscript; gutter: false; theme: Django" data-theme=3D"Django">=3D=3D=3D=3D=
 Welcome to your Dev VM =3D=3D=3D=3D
City: &lt;city&gt;
Weather today: &lt;curl output&gt;
Hostname: &lt;hostname&gt;
Time: &lt;timestamp&gt;
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-ServiceStatus">Service Stat=
us</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>systemctl status weather.service</code> must show <code>active (ex=
ited)</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Changing <code>CITY</code> in <code>/etc/default/weather</code> + restar=
ting the service must update MOTD</p></li>
<li>
<p>MOTD =3D MESSAGE OF THE DAY</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-=F0=9F=93=81Deliverables">=
=F0=9F=93=81 Deliverables</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-CodeFiles">Code Files</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><code>/usr/local/sbin/weather.sh</code> (executable, readable, idempoten=
t)</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>/etc/systemd/system/weather.service</code> (unit file)</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>/etc/default/weather</code> (environment configuration)</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-Documentation">Documentatio=
n</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>README.md</strong>: Clear instructions on how to install, enable=
, and verify</p></li>
<li>
<p>Example output of MOTD after running</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-=F0=9F=9B=A1=EF=B8=8FGoodPr=
actices">=F0=9F=9B=A1=EF=B8=8F Good Practices</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Script is safe (uses <code>set -euo pipefail</code>)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Commands are logged (simple echo statements OK)</p></li>
<li>
<p>MOTD is always clean (no appending duplicates)</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DevOpsonLinuxProject-WeatherVMProject-=F0=9F=A7=A9BonusFeatures(O=
ptionalforExtraPoints)">=F0=9F=A7=A9 Bonus Features (Optional for Extra Poi=
nts)</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Add uptime or disk usage info into MOTD</p></li>
<li>
<p>Log weather fetches into <code>/var/log/weather.log</code></p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
